1
00:01:37,708 --> 00:01:38,625
[MARI]
Hey, Yuri.

2
00:01:38,708 --> 00:01:39,750
Makka got into
the steamed buns,

3
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:41,250
and one of 'em got
stuck in his throat.

4
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:44,041
[YURI] Victor! You need
to get back to Japan.

5
00:01:44,125 --> 00:01:45,583
It will just be for tomorrow.

6
00:01:45,666 --> 00:01:48,000
One day only, will you
be Yuri's coach?

7
00:01:48,083 --> 00:01:48,833
Huh?

8
00:01:48,916 --> 00:01:50,500
--Huh?
--[PLISETSKY] Huh?

9
00:01:50,583 --> 00:01:52,875
[YURI] I can't believe
this is actually happening.

10
00:01:52,958 --> 00:01:56,125
Ask Yakov if you need help
or don't understand something.

11
00:01:56,208 --> 00:01:57,541
If you're in trouble,
just hug him,

12
00:01:57,625 --> 00:01:59,791
and he'll be there for you.

13
00:01:59,875 --> 00:02:01,291
I'm sorry, Yuri.

14
00:02:01,375 --> 00:02:05,625
I know I won't be here,
but I'll be with you in spirit.

15
00:02:05,708 --> 00:02:10,000
[YURI] And then,
Victor went back to Japan.

16
00:02:10,083 --> 00:02:12,333
"Yuri vs. Yuri. The Horror!

17
00:02:12,416 --> 00:02:14,416
Rostelecom Cup, Free Skate."

18
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:16,250
It didn't look like you
talked to Coach Yakov

19
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:17,833
too much during this
morning's practice.

20
00:02:17,916 --> 00:02:19,541
How do you feel about that?

21
00:02:19,625 --> 00:02:21,291
I don't think it's a big deal.

22
00:02:21,375 --> 00:02:24,375
I'll skate like I always have
with Victor, and it'll be fine.

23
00:02:24,458 --> 00:02:27,333
[PLISETSKY] Why did Yakov
take on the pork cutlet bowl?

24
00:02:27,416 --> 00:02:28,583
[YAKOV]
Yuri.

25
00:02:28,666 --> 00:02:31,916
Your grandfather's here
if you want to see him.

26
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,291
[PLISETSKY]
Why are you here?

27
00:02:33,375 --> 00:02:35,250
I didn't think you
were feeling well.

28
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:37,208
[GRANDPA PLISETSKY]
Hush, now. Just eat.

29
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:38,416
[grunts]

30
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:40,291
[PLISETSKY]
Pork, scrambled eggs, and rice?

31
00:02:40,375 --> 00:02:41,666
What kind of pirozhki is this?

32
00:02:41,750 --> 00:02:43,666
A pork cutlet bowl pirozhki.

33
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:46,916
Eat them and do your best
in the free skate, Yurochka.

34
00:02:48,166 --> 00:02:49,666
Da.

35
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:51,708
[PLISETSKY] With Victor gone,
I'm the only one

36
00:02:51,791 --> 00:02:53,041
who can win for Russia.

37
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:54,625
Now's my chance to prove myself.

38
00:02:55,666 --> 00:02:57,166
[MOROOKA] Group Two
is about to take the ice


39
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:59,250
here at the Rostelecom
Cup in Moscow,


40
00:02:59,333 --> 00:03:01,750
the final event of
the Grand Prix Series.


41
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:03,500
Each skater came
into this competition

42
00:03:03,583 --> 00:03:05,833
with his own hopes and fears,
as it will determine

43
00:03:05,916 --> 00:03:07,750
who advances to the
Grand Prix Final.

44
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:10,041
First up in Group Two,
currently in sixth place,

45
00:03:10,125 --> 00:03:12,583
is the Czech Republic's
Emil Nekola.

46
00:03:12,666 --> 00:03:14,333
[electronic music plays]

47
00:03:14,416 --> 00:03:16,375
[MOROOKA] He is skating to music
from the movie <i>Anastasis</i> .

48
00:03:16,458 --> 00:03:17,791
His theme for this season:

49
00:03:17,875 --> 00:03:20,250
"Cyberpunk: I've
ceased to be human."

50
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:23,041
Just as the theme suggests,
he plans four quads,

51
00:03:23,125 --> 00:03:25,125
a superhuman feat.

52
00:03:25,208 --> 00:03:27,291
That was a beautiful
quadruple Salchow.

53
00:03:27,375 --> 00:03:28,750
And well done!

54
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:37,625
[MOROOKA] Next up is a
quadruple toe loop combination.

55
00:03:37,708 --> 00:03:38,833
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
Quadruple toe loop...

56
00:03:38,916 --> 00:03:40,083
Triple toe loop.

57
00:03:40,166 --> 00:03:42,500
I need to say something
before you go out there.

58
00:03:42,583 --> 00:03:44,958
I'm going to make it to
the Grand Prix Final, Mickey,

59
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:46,583
with or without you.

60
00:03:46,666 --> 00:03:48,125
It's time for you
to learn how to skate

61
00:03:48,208 --> 00:03:50,250
without me there to support you.

62
00:03:56,541 --> 00:03:59,541
[MOROOKA] His next jump
will also be a quad.

63
00:03:59,625 --> 00:04:00,666
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A quadruple toe loop.

64
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:02,250
[MOROOKA]
That was brilliant!

65
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,625
[SARA]
Take a look around, will you?

66
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:11,791
I'm not the only
woman in the world!

67
00:04:11,875 --> 00:04:14,625
Maybe not, but you're
the only woman I care about!

68
00:04:14,708 --> 00:04:16,750
I've only come this
far because of you--

69
00:04:16,833 --> 00:04:19,250
how can I keep
skating if you go?

70
00:04:19,333 --> 00:04:21,708
Please don't leave me, Sara!

71
00:04:21,791 --> 00:04:23,125
[SARA]
Learn how to be strong,

72
00:04:23,208 --> 00:04:25,041
because, not only am I
going to skate without you,

73
00:04:25,125 --> 00:04:26,958
I'm going to start dating.

74
00:04:27,041 --> 00:04:28,458
[MOROOKA]
If he finishes second or above,

75
00:04:28,541 --> 00:04:31,833
he may still make
the Grand Prix Final.

76
00:04:31,916 --> 00:04:32,958
[MICHELE]
Do you like Czech men

77
00:04:33,041 --> 00:04:35,000
who smile and laugh
all the time?

78
00:04:35,083 --> 00:04:36,583
Is that it?

79
00:04:36,666 --> 00:04:39,916
Or do you prefer moody Japanese
men who look like closet pervs?

80
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,666
What do they have to offer?

81
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:43,958
How can any of them
be worthy of you?

82
00:04:44,041 --> 00:04:44,916
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A quadruple loop.

83
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,458
[MOROOKA]
That was perfect!

84
00:04:46,541 --> 00:04:49,708
He's given us four flawless
quads in this program so far.

85
00:04:49,791 --> 00:04:51,416
[MICHELE]
He really isn't human.

86
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,291
[EMIL]
Man, I'm getting tired.

87
00:04:53,375 --> 00:04:54,541
[MICHELE gasps]

88
00:04:56,625 --> 00:04:58,000
[grunts]

89
00:04:58,083 --> 00:04:59,500
[ANNOUNCER 8A] Ah... He'd
planned a combination there.

90
00:04:59,583 --> 00:05:01,583
[MOROOKA] He fell and couldn't
complete the second jump.

91
00:05:01,666 --> 00:05:04,083
[EMIL]
Crap, that was bad!

92
00:05:04,166 --> 00:05:05,541
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple Salchow.

93
00:05:05,625 --> 00:05:06,583
[MICHELE]
Oops.

94
00:05:06,666 --> 00:05:08,666
[EMIL]
Still going!

95
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:11,208
[AUDIENCE cheering]

96
00:05:12,583 --> 00:05:15,208
[AUDIENCE cheers]

97
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:17,916
[panting]

98
00:05:18,791 --> 00:05:22,666
[MOROOKA] The score for
Emil Nekola is 189.15.


99
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:25,708
His total score is 271.58.


100
00:05:25,791 --> 00:05:28,916
Aren't you usually rinkside
to send him off to the ice?

101
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,750
[MOROOKA] Next up is
Michele Crispino, age 22.

102
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:34,500
He finished the
short program in fifth.

103
00:05:34,583 --> 00:05:36,541
Will he make a comeback
in the free skate?

104
00:05:36,625 --> 00:05:38,000
["Serenade for Two" plays]

105
00:05:38,083 --> 00:05:41,041
[MOROOKA] He is skating
to "Serenade for Two."

106
00:05:42,666 --> 00:05:45,083
[MICHELE] Sara, you're
out there somewhere,

107
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:46,916
watching me, aren't you?

108
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:51,208
Even though we're apart,
I can still feel your eyes.

109
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:54,916
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A quadruple Salchow.

110
00:05:56,916 --> 00:05:58,625
[SARA]
He looks a little sad out there.

111
00:05:58,708 --> 00:06:00,125
I hope he holds up.

112
00:06:00,208 --> 00:06:05,208
["Serenade for Two" continues]

113
00:06:12,291 --> 00:06:14,833
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
Triple flip, single loop...

114
00:06:14,916 --> 00:06:15,875
...and a triple Salchow!

115
00:06:15,958 --> 00:06:18,125
[MOROOKA]
A three-jump combo!

116
00:06:18,208 --> 00:06:20,541
[MICHELE] What should I do
with my feelings?

117
00:06:20,625 --> 00:06:23,416
I guess... I could skate them?

118
00:06:26,458 --> 00:06:28,333
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple axel.

119
00:06:28,416 --> 00:06:31,000
[SARA] His skating is more
mellow than in practice.

120
00:06:31,083 --> 00:06:32,500
Less high-strung.

121
00:06:33,541 --> 00:06:35,208
He's like a different
person today.

122
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:36,541
Where'd that come from?

123
00:06:36,625 --> 00:06:38,041
Love.

124
00:06:38,125 --> 00:06:39,875
Can't you see it? It's so clear.

125
00:06:39,958 --> 00:06:43,125
His skating is filled
with the pain of lost love.

126
00:06:44,791 --> 00:06:46,375
[MICHELE]
What's changed?

127
00:06:46,458 --> 00:06:49,041
We've been inseparable
our whole lives.

128
00:06:49,125 --> 00:06:53,333
My precious Sara. My lady.

129
00:06:53,416 --> 00:06:54,458
[SARA]
I don't understand!

130
00:06:54,541 --> 00:06:56,500
Why are boys so mean to me?

131
00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:59,000
[MICHELE]
It's because you're so cute.

132
00:06:59,083 --> 00:07:00,833
Don't worry,
I beat them all up!

133
00:07:00,916 --> 00:07:02,833
[SARA] Another guy
wants to go out with me.

134
00:07:02,916 --> 00:07:04,666
[MICHELE]
I'll beat them all up!

135
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:09,166
I can see it now.
I've been an idiot, haven't I?

136
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:13,833
[gasps]

137
00:07:15,625 --> 00:07:18,416
[MICHELE]
Sara. This is it.

138
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:21,000
This is the last time
I skate for you.

139
00:07:22,625 --> 00:07:27,041
[MICHELE] It's over.
I have to accept that.

140
00:07:27,125 --> 00:07:29,875
I'll show you
how much I love you

141
00:07:29,958 --> 00:07:32,666
by letting you go.

142
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:35,458
Goodbye, Sara.

143
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:45,000
[SARA sobbing]

144
00:07:46,583 --> 00:07:48,083
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple Lutz.

145
00:07:52,208 --> 00:07:54,000
Amazing! That was flawless!

146
00:07:54,083 --> 00:07:54,750
[SARA gasps]

147
00:07:54,833 --> 00:07:56,666
[gasps]

148
00:07:56,750 --> 00:08:02,833
[AUDIENCE cheers]

149
00:08:05,291 --> 00:08:08,291
[MOROOKA] Here come the scores
for Michele Crispino of Italy.

150
00:08:08,375 --> 00:08:13,833
One ninty-three point two four!
His total score was 282.89.


151
00:08:13,916 --> 00:08:14,916
A new personal best!


152
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,000
[MOROKA]
He's surpassed his personal best


153
00:08:16,083 --> 00:08:17,833
--by nearly 20 points!
--[SARA] Mickey!

154
00:08:19,250 --> 00:08:21,166
[MICHELE]
Sara!

155
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:22,625
[SARA]
Congratulations!

156
00:08:22,708 --> 00:08:24,041
I'm so proud!

157
00:08:24,125 --> 00:08:27,083
That was by far the best program
I've ever seen you do.

158
00:08:27,166 --> 00:08:28,750
You were thinking
about me, weren't you?

159
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:30,416
[MICHELE]
Eh, <i>si</i> ?

160
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:33,083
[SARA] I'm sorry for saying
such mean things to you earlier.

161
00:08:33,166 --> 00:08:34,541
But I'm glad I did!

162
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:37,333
We're better off apart,
and now you can see it, too!

163
00:08:37,416 --> 00:08:38,583
Heh?

164
00:08:38,666 --> 00:08:40,958
Oh, Looks like Seung Gil's
starting. See ya!

165
00:08:41,041 --> 00:08:44,291
[somber music playing]

166
00:08:44,375 --> 00:08:46,625
[SEUNG GIL grunts]

167
00:08:46,708 --> 00:08:48,666
[SEUNG GIL growls]

168
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:49,500
[PLISETSKY]
Hey, Yakov.

169
00:08:49,583 --> 00:08:50,500
What is it?

170
00:08:50,583 --> 00:08:52,583
I'm changing the
jump composition.

171
00:08:52,666 --> 00:08:53,458
Huh?

172
00:08:53,541 --> 00:08:54,541
I'll reduce the number of jumps

173
00:08:54,625 --> 00:08:56,208
in the first half
from four to two.

174
00:08:56,291 --> 00:08:58,208
So you'll have six
in the second half?

175
00:08:58,291 --> 00:08:59,083
That's right.

176
00:08:59,166 --> 00:09:00,708
That's suicide.

177
00:09:00,791 --> 00:09:03,916
[PLISETSKY] It's the only way
I can win against JJ and Yuri.

178
00:09:10,166 --> 00:09:12,083
[MOROOKA] Although Seung Gil
recovered after a fall


179
00:09:12,166 --> 00:09:14,875
on his early quadruple loop,
he suffered a huge loss


180
00:09:14,958 --> 00:09:16,625
in the standings and has no hope

181
00:09:16,708 --> 00:09:18,375
of advancing to
the Grand Prix Final.

182
00:09:18,458 --> 00:09:19,750
Though, we look
forward to seeing him

183
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:22,500
at the Four Continents
Championship.

184
00:09:22,583 --> 00:09:23,916
[gasps]

185
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,666
[MOROOKA] Here on his home turf,
we have Yuri Plisetzky,

186
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:28,833
age 15, in third place
after the short program.

187
00:09:28,916 --> 00:09:31,166
--Just listen to those cheers!
--[AUDIENCE] Yuri! Yuri! Yuri!

188
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:32,958
[PLISETSKY]
I am going to win the first gold

189
00:09:33,041 --> 00:09:35,333
of my senior division
debut season.

190
00:09:35,416 --> 00:09:37,666
["Allegro Appassionato
in B Minor" plays]

191
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:38,708
[MOROOKA]
He is skating to

192
00:09:38,791 --> 00:09:41,125
"Allegro Appassionato
in B Minor."

193
00:09:41,208 --> 00:09:44,208
The program was choreographed
by Lilia Baranovskaya,

194
00:09:44,291 --> 00:09:47,041
former prima ballerina
of the Bolshoi Ballet.

195
00:09:47,125 --> 00:09:49,291
For his senior debut,
they've chosen a piece

196
00:09:49,375 --> 00:09:52,375
well known for its
difficulty and intensity.

197
00:09:52,458 --> 00:09:54,125
This is the first season
he's been allowed

198
00:09:54,208 --> 00:09:57,625
to attempt quads. Here's the
first of two in this program.

199
00:09:57,708 --> 00:10:00,208
He landed that with
confidence and precision.

200
00:10:00,291 --> 00:10:05,166
["Allegro Appassionato
in B Minor" continues]

201
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:07,333
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple axel from a spiral.

202
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:09,666
That was high.

203
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:11,458
Is he pushing himself too hard?

204
00:10:11,541 --> 00:10:14,583
Yes. Dance with beauty.

205
00:10:14,666 --> 00:10:18,041
Most people don't realize beauty
is a force of righteousness.

206
00:10:18,125 --> 00:10:21,041
Without beauty,
strength means nothing.

207
00:10:31,375 --> 00:10:34,708
[YURI] A hellish step sequence
without even time for a breath.

208
00:10:34,791 --> 00:10:36,750
How is he so calm?

209
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:39,250
[YAKOV] This is about
when he starts to tire.

210
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:42,208
Hold up in the
second half, Yuri.

211
00:10:42,291 --> 00:10:44,750
[PLISETSKY]
Damn. This is tough.

212
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:46,125
[gasps]

213
00:10:46,208 --> 00:10:48,208
[MIRA] He's putting six jumps
in the second half?

214
00:10:48,291 --> 00:10:50,500
[PLISETSKY]
All right, here we go.

215
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:52,916
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple Lutz.

216
00:10:57,291 --> 00:11:01,250
[PLISETSKY] Pork cutlet bowl has
three quads and JJ has four.

217
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:04,458
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple flip.

218
00:11:09,083 --> 00:11:12,666
[PLISETSKY] To beat them,
I can't make any mistakes.

219
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,666
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A quadruple toe loop.

220
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:18,500
And next up, we have
a choreographic sequence.

221
00:11:18,583 --> 00:11:21,041
[PLISETSKY] I don't want
to lose like that again.

222
00:11:21,125 --> 00:11:24,083
[MOROOKA] With all eyes on him,
Yuri Plisetsky of Russia,

223
00:11:24,166 --> 00:11:27,750
age 15, has completed
an excellent free skate.

224
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:29,041
[PLISETSKY]
Huh?!

225
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:34,958
Let's meet again on the podium
at the Rostelecom Cup, Yuri.

226
00:11:35,041 --> 00:11:36,208
See you there.

227
00:11:36,291 --> 00:11:37,583
Shithead!

228
00:11:37,666 --> 00:11:39,791
[ANNOUNCER 8A] Quadruple
Salchow, triple toe loop.

229
00:11:39,875 --> 00:11:42,291
[MOROOKA] That was a beautiful
jump with impressive height.

230
00:11:42,375 --> 00:11:45,333
He's showing no signs of
slowing down in the second half.

231
00:11:54,375 --> 00:11:57,041
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple loop, double toe loop.

232
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:01,750
[PLISETSKY]
The last jump combination.

233
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:04,375
He's changed... so much.

234
00:12:04,458 --> 00:12:06,666
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple axel, single loop,

235
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:07,875
and a triple Salchow!

236
00:12:07,958 --> 00:12:10,666
[MOROOKA] That's it,
he landed all his jumps!

237
00:12:12,375 --> 00:12:13,875
[MOROOKA]
He refused to give into pressure

238
00:12:13,958 --> 00:12:15,375
here at the Rostelecom Cup,

239
00:12:15,458 --> 00:12:17,500
instead responding
to his local fans

240
00:12:17,583 --> 00:12:20,708
and delivering a sublime
free skate program!

241
00:12:20,791 --> 00:12:23,250
Russia must be proud today!

242
00:12:29,416 --> 00:12:33,750
[AUDIENCE cheers]

243
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:35,416
[PLISETSKY pants]

244
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:39,000
[YURI] A performance beyond
his limits. That's what it was.

245
00:12:39,083 --> 00:12:43,291
[MOROOKA] Yuri Plisetsky's
free skate score is 199.87,


246
00:12:43,375 --> 00:12:48,541
a personal best.
His total score is 297.96.


247
00:12:48,625 --> 00:12:51,041
He is currently in first place,
and has earned himself

248
00:12:51,125 --> 00:12:52,375
a ticket to the
Grand Prix Final!

249
00:12:52,458 --> 00:12:54,541
How'd you like my free skate,
pork cutlet bowl?

250
00:13:01,791 --> 00:13:03,750
["Yuri on Ice" plays]

251
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:05,458
[MOROOKA]
Yuri Katsuki is in second place

252
00:13:05,541 --> 00:13:07,166
after the short program.

253
00:13:07,250 --> 00:13:10,375
He is skating to "Yuri on Ice."

254
00:13:10,458 --> 00:13:13,125
["Yuri on Ice" continues]

255
00:13:13,208 --> 00:13:15,166
[YURI] I don't want people
to think that everything

256
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:19,041
Victor's taught me so far
has been a waste.

257
00:13:19,125 --> 00:13:21,916
I have to prove
myself by winning.

258
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:25,375
If I fail here,
everything is over.

259
00:13:25,458 --> 00:13:26,375
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A quadruple toe loop.

260
00:13:26,458 --> 00:13:27,708
[YURI]
I popped it!

261
00:13:27,791 --> 00:13:29,375
What is that idiot doing?

262
00:13:29,458 --> 00:13:31,333
[MOROOKA] His second jump
turned into a single.

263
00:13:31,416 --> 00:13:32,791
[YURI]
Damn it!

264
00:13:32,875 --> 00:13:35,708
Calm down. Calm down.

265
00:13:38,458 --> 00:13:40,750
[YURI]
How do I recover from this?

266
00:13:42,375 --> 00:13:44,125
I've noticed you tend
to flub your jumps

267
00:13:44,208 --> 00:13:45,375
when there's something
on your mind.

268
00:13:45,458 --> 00:13:46,708
Care to share?

269
00:13:46,791 --> 00:13:48,750
Starting today, I'm going
to be your new coach.

270
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:50,791
And you're going to win.

271
00:13:52,541 --> 00:13:56,291
[YURI] Somehow, he seemed
to know how I felt.

272
00:13:56,375 --> 00:13:57,916
Until Victor came into my life,

273
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:01,333
I never went around saying
I was going to win gold.

274
00:14:01,416 --> 00:14:05,000
But whether I said it or not,
it's what I was skating for.

275
00:14:05,083 --> 00:14:06,041
[MOROOKA]
That jump had enough rotations.

276
00:14:06,125 --> 00:14:07,250
[PLISETSKY growls]

277
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:08,791
[YURI]
Honestly, I wanted to win gold

278
00:14:08,875 --> 00:14:11,625
at last year's
Grand Prix Final, too.

279
00:14:11,708 --> 00:14:13,875
You aren't a weak person, Yuri.

280
00:14:13,958 --> 00:14:16,791
Nobody who knows you
would ever think that.

281
00:14:16,875 --> 00:14:19,250
It's changed me.
I'm stronger now.

282
00:14:19,333 --> 00:14:21,458
And I'll prove it
at the Grand Prix Final

283
00:14:21,541 --> 00:14:23,625
with a gold medal!

284
00:14:23,708 --> 00:14:26,583
I made it this far because
Victor believed in me.

285
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:27,666
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple loop.

286
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:28,875
[YURI]
What happens if it ends here?

287
00:14:28,958 --> 00:14:30,250
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
He two-footed that landing.

288
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:31,416
[YURI] If I don't make
it to the Grand Prix Final?

289
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:33,958
No, stop it.
Don't think right now.

290
00:14:34,041 --> 00:14:35,291
Idiot! Come on--!

291
00:14:35,375 --> 00:14:36,750
[whistles]

292
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:37,791
Ah...

293
00:14:37,875 --> 00:14:39,833
How nice. All supportive

294
00:14:39,916 --> 00:14:42,125
now that you've clenched
your spot in the final.

295
00:14:42,208 --> 00:14:44,125
Are you going to
cheer for me, too?

296
00:14:44,208 --> 00:14:44,791
[PLISETSKY growls]

297
00:14:44,875 --> 00:14:46,958
Yuri. Let's go.

298
00:14:47,041 --> 00:14:49,291
[YURI] Yurio looked like
that last three-jump combo

299
00:14:49,375 --> 00:14:51,041
was going to kill him.

300
00:14:51,125 --> 00:14:54,875
That idiot. He doesn't have
as much stamina as I do!

301
00:14:54,958 --> 00:14:56,250
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple axel.

302
00:15:00,125 --> 00:15:03,541
[YURI] Whether Victor's
here or I'm alone,

303
00:15:03,625 --> 00:15:05,458
it's still just as difficult.

304
00:15:05,541 --> 00:15:07,958
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple flip.

305
00:15:08,041 --> 00:15:10,166
[YURI]
I just need to keep it simple.

306
00:15:10,250 --> 00:15:12,500
This program is me.

307
00:15:12,583 --> 00:15:15,375
Nobody else can skate it
the way I can.

308
00:15:18,375 --> 00:15:20,541
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple axel, single loop,

309
00:15:20,625 --> 00:15:21,666
and triple Salchow.

310
00:15:21,750 --> 00:15:23,166
[gasps]

311
00:15:27,625 --> 00:15:30,958
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple Lutz, triple toe loop.

312
00:15:31,041 --> 00:15:34,166
[YURI] Victor and I created
this program together

313
00:15:34,250 --> 00:15:37,083
and I love it so much it hurts.

314
00:15:38,458 --> 00:15:40,166
[YURI]
I'm not finished yet.

315
00:15:40,250 --> 00:15:44,208
I won't be done until
I get the gold with Victor.

316
00:15:44,291 --> 00:15:45,791
[MOROOKA] In this step
sequence, you can feel

317
00:15:45,875 --> 00:15:49,833
Yuri Katsuki's love, a love
he can only express on the ice.

318
00:15:58,083 --> 00:16:01,083
[AUDIENCE cheers]

319
00:16:01,166 --> 00:16:04,208
Aw. He had really good
flow up until the end.

320
00:16:04,291 --> 00:16:05,666
Da. You know,

321
00:16:05,750 --> 00:16:07,958
when you think of how it
could've been with Victor here,

322
00:16:08,041 --> 00:16:10,083
you want to see that.

323
00:16:10,166 --> 00:16:15,208
[AUDIENCE cheers]

324
00:16:15,291 --> 00:16:20,250
[AUDIENCE cheers]

325
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:23,791
[YAKOV growls]

326
00:16:23,875 --> 00:16:26,000
[pants]

327
00:16:26,083 --> 00:16:28,083
[YURI] That's the hardest
I've ever pushed myself

328
00:16:28,166 --> 00:16:29,833
to complete a program.

329
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:33,500
[YAKOV]
Hey.

330
00:16:33,583 --> 00:16:35,708
Vitya designed that
program for you,

331
00:16:35,791 --> 00:16:37,958
yet you failed to
take advantage of it.

332
00:16:38,041 --> 00:16:39,708
You'd've been better
prepared if you practiced

333
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:40,791
for the possibility you might...

334
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:43,041
[YURI]
A lecture at the kiss and cry.

335
00:16:43,125 --> 00:16:44,916
This is where Victor learned it.

336
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:48,791
[MOROOKA] Yuri Katsuki's score
for the free skate is 172.87,


337
00:16:48,875 --> 00:16:51,916
bringing his total
score to 282.84.


338
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,500
He is currently in third place.

339
00:16:53,583 --> 00:16:55,333
He may yet advance to
the Grand Prix Final,

340
00:16:55,416 --> 00:16:56,833
but we won't know until the end.

341
00:16:56,916 --> 00:16:59,416
Interesting, that's a
higher score than I expected.

342
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:00,250
[YURI sighs]

343
00:17:00,333 --> 00:17:02,833
[YAKOV]
Hm? What's wrong?

344
00:17:02,916 --> 00:17:04,416
[YURI]
<i>Spasibo</i> .

345
00:17:06,666 --> 00:17:09,291
[YURI] Victor will be going
back to Russia before long.

346
00:17:09,375 --> 00:17:12,500
[MOROOKA] The final skater
is Jean-Jacques Leroy, age 19.

347
00:17:12,583 --> 00:17:15,041
[JEAN-JACQUES]
Finally. I was tired of waiting.

348
00:17:15,125 --> 00:17:16,833
I'm sure the audience was, too.

349
00:17:16,916 --> 00:17:19,500
["Partizan Hope" plays]

350
00:17:19,583 --> 00:17:22,583
[MOROOKA] He will be skating
to "Partizan Hope."

351
00:17:24,208 --> 00:17:25,833
[JEAN-JACQUES]
Yuri Katsuki.

352
00:17:25,916 --> 00:17:29,250
Victor may have chosen you,
but you're no king.

353
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:32,416
I can tell that much
from your free skate.

354
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:34,208
I'm the only king here.

355
00:17:34,291 --> 00:17:36,958
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A quadruple Salchow.

356
00:17:37,041 --> 00:17:39,208
[MOROOKA] He's planned four
quads for this program.

357
00:17:39,291 --> 00:17:40,791
If he follows through
on all of them,

358
00:17:40,875 --> 00:17:43,208
his free skate program will have
the highest technical difficulty

359
00:17:43,291 --> 00:17:46,250
of all the skaters
competing here today.

360
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:49,166
Next up, we're looking for
a quad-triple combination.

361
00:17:50,458 --> 00:17:51,791
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
Quadruple toe loop,

362
00:17:51,875 --> 00:17:53,916
triple toe loop.

363
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,208
At Skate Canada,
he held off Russia's star

364
00:17:56,291 --> 00:17:58,791
Yuri Plisetsky to
claim first place.

365
00:17:58,875 --> 00:18:01,333
He came in third at last
year's Grand Prix Final.

366
00:18:01,416 --> 00:18:03,291
With Victor Nikiforov
absent this season,

367
00:18:03,375 --> 00:18:05,458
it seems a new prince in
the figure skating world

368
00:18:05,541 --> 00:18:06,958
has been born.

369
00:18:08,291 --> 00:18:09,625
[JEAN-JACQUES]
That's where you're wrong.

370
00:18:09,708 --> 00:18:13,083
I'm no prince.
I'm already a king!

371
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:16,666
[JEAN-JACQUES]
When I designed this program,

372
00:18:16,750 --> 00:18:19,875
I thought to myself, "I'll be
the one who stops Victor

373
00:18:19,958 --> 00:18:21,666
from claiming a
sixth consecutive

374
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:23,500
world-championship title."

375
00:18:23,583 --> 00:18:26,083
Of course, I didn't
know he'd quit.

376
00:18:26,166 --> 00:18:29,916
I bet he ran because he was
afraid of losing to me.

377
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:31,708
I almost pity him.

378
00:18:31,791 --> 00:18:33,500
Poor little Victor.

379
00:18:35,333 --> 00:18:36,916
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple axel.

380
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:40,000
[JEAN-JACQUES] Mom and Dad,
my precious girlfriend,

381
00:18:40,083 --> 00:18:43,875
the great people
of Canada, my fans,

382
00:18:43,958 --> 00:18:46,916
and everyone in the world
who loves skating.

383
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,583
This is for you!

384
00:18:48,666 --> 00:18:50,000
But it's not enough--

385
00:18:50,083 --> 00:18:51,500
I have more love to give!

386
00:18:51,583 --> 00:18:52,583
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A quadruple Lutz!

387
00:18:52,666 --> 00:18:54,208
[MOROOKA]
Nice landing!

388
00:18:55,541 --> 00:18:56,333
[JEAN-JACQUES]
It's not just that

389
00:18:56,416 --> 00:18:59,083
I land all my jumps with ease.

390
00:18:59,166 --> 00:19:03,041
I also make sure they blend
into the overall performance.

391
00:19:03,125 --> 00:19:05,791
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple flip, single loop...

392
00:19:05,875 --> 00:19:07,041
...and triple Salchow!

393
00:19:07,125 --> 00:19:09,708
[MOROOKA] Amazing!
A superb jump combination!

394
00:19:09,791 --> 00:19:13,250
[JEAN-JACQUES]
Hey, judges! This is JJ!

395
00:19:13,333 --> 00:19:14,875
His last jump will be a quad.

396
00:19:14,958 --> 00:19:16,583
Will he stick this one, too?

397
00:19:16,666 --> 00:19:18,458
[JEAN-JACQUES]
Let's go!

398
00:19:18,541 --> 00:19:19,666
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A quadruple toe loop!

399
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:22,625
[MOROOKA] That's it!
He landed all his jumps!

400
00:19:22,708 --> 00:19:25,083
That seals the deal.
He'll take first.

401
00:19:25,166 --> 00:19:26,625
Yuri Plisetsky will take second,

402
00:19:26,708 --> 00:19:28,625
and Michele Crispino
will place third.

403
00:19:28,708 --> 00:19:30,166
[REPORTER 9C]
Fourth is Yuri Katsuki.

404
00:19:30,250 --> 00:19:32,041
[REPORTER 9A] When you total
both competition scores,

405
00:19:32,125 --> 00:19:35,000
Crispino and Katsuki are tied.

406
00:19:35,083 --> 00:19:36,958
[YURI]
We're tied in points,

407
00:19:37,041 --> 00:19:38,875
but I'll squeak into
the Grand Prix Final

408
00:19:38,958 --> 00:19:41,458
since I took second
at the Cup of China.

409
00:19:41,541 --> 00:19:44,375
[AUDIENCE cheering]

410
00:19:44,458 --> 00:19:45,916
[sighs]

411
00:19:47,875 --> 00:19:50,833
[YURI]
The Rostelecom Cup is over.

412
00:19:50,916 --> 00:19:53,125
The final six who will advance
to the Grand Prix Final

413
00:19:53,208 --> 00:19:56,291
are the three who had basically
been confirmed already.

414
00:19:56,375 --> 00:19:59,500
JJ, who cemented his win with
another high score, Yurio,

415
00:19:59,583 --> 00:20:01,541
who place second. And...

416
00:20:01,625 --> 00:20:03,833
[sighs] I'm exhausted.

417
00:20:03,916 --> 00:20:05,333
Then you should get some rest.

418
00:20:05,416 --> 00:20:07,375
Don't worry about the
women's free skate tomorrow.

419
00:20:07,458 --> 00:20:08,541
I'll be fine.

420
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:09,916
What, I can't even
come to cheer you on?

421
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,708
You would rush straight
to the kiss and cry.

422
00:20:11,791 --> 00:20:12,875
[BOTH gasp]

423
00:20:12,958 --> 00:20:14,208
Hey, Yuri!

424
00:20:14,291 --> 00:20:15,916
Congrats on qualifying.

425
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,583
I knew you would
make it to the final.

426
00:20:17,666 --> 00:20:18,875
Sara!

427
00:20:18,958 --> 00:20:20,208
--[SARA gasps]
--[YURI] Thank you.

428
00:20:20,291 --> 00:20:22,875
[gasps] What in the hell
do you think you're doing?

429
00:20:22,958 --> 00:20:24,041
Eh?

430
00:20:24,125 --> 00:20:25,666
[screams]

431
00:20:25,750 --> 00:20:27,375
Was that Mickey screaming?

432
00:20:27,458 --> 00:20:29,666
Are we having a
hugging competition now?

433
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:30,791
[YURI]
Hm...

434
00:20:30,875 --> 00:20:31,750
[SEUNG GIL whimpers]

435
00:20:31,833 --> 00:20:33,291
Y'see, JJ style is--

436
00:20:33,375 --> 00:20:34,458
Mm...

437
00:20:34,541 --> 00:20:40,375
No! Stay away from me!

438
00:20:40,458 --> 00:20:42,375
[ALL but YURI sigh]

439
00:20:44,208 --> 00:20:45,416
[YURI]
I'm this close to the end

440
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:48,166
of my competitive
figure skating career.

441
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:50,333
I really want the gold now.

442
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:53,916
The Grand Prix Final
will be my last chance.

443
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:56,500
Even if I don't
take first place,

444
00:20:56,583 --> 00:21:00,208
I'll have Victor step down
as my coach after the final,

445
00:21:00,291 --> 00:21:01,250
and then--

446
00:21:01,333 --> 00:21:02,291
[YURI yelps]

447
00:21:03,541 --> 00:21:05,375
[PLISETSKY]
There you are, pork cutlet bowl.

448
00:21:05,458 --> 00:21:06,583
I've been looking for you.

449
00:21:06,666 --> 00:21:08,000
[YURI]
Uh, hey, Yurio.

450
00:21:08,083 --> 00:21:09,708
[PLISETSKY] What was with
all that hugging earlier?

451
00:21:09,791 --> 00:21:11,083
Stop creeping me out!

452
00:21:11,166 --> 00:21:12,833
And your free skate
was pathetic!

453
00:21:12,916 --> 00:21:14,833
You get to make the excuse
that you didn't do your best

454
00:21:14,916 --> 00:21:16,833
because Victor wasn't there.

455
00:21:16,916 --> 00:21:19,083
But I was in top form
skating out there today

456
00:21:19,166 --> 00:21:23,458
and earned a new personal best
only to lose to JJ again!

457
00:21:23,541 --> 00:21:24,541
You have no right

458
00:21:24,625 --> 00:21:26,541
to be more pissed off
than me, okay?

459
00:21:28,458 --> 00:21:29,541
[YURI]
Uh--

460
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:30,708
That's for you.

461
00:21:30,791 --> 00:21:32,416
It's almost your
birthday, right?

462
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:33,666
[YURI]
Huh?

463
00:21:35,708 --> 00:21:38,208
[YURI gasps]
Pirozhki?

464
00:21:38,291 --> 00:21:39,041
Eat.

465
00:21:39,125 --> 00:21:40,125
[YURI]
What, right now?

466
00:21:40,208 --> 00:21:41,583
Yes, now!

467
00:21:43,791 --> 00:21:47,708
Hey, there's rice in here.
Pork and egg, too.

468
00:21:47,791 --> 00:21:48,750
Wait, is this...?

469
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:50,041
Da!

470
00:21:50,125 --> 00:21:51,666
My grandpa made them himself!

471
00:21:51,750 --> 00:21:52,625
Aren't they great?

472
00:21:52,708 --> 00:21:55,041
Yeah! They're <i>vkusno</i> !

473
00:21:57,208 --> 00:22:00,208
[YURI] There's so much
I wanna tell you, Victor.

474
00:22:00,291 --> 00:22:02,958
What do I say first?

475
00:22:03,041 --> 00:22:04,250
[MAKKACHIN barks]

476
00:22:06,875 --> 00:22:08,333
[YURI gasps]

477
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:13,250
[panting]

478
00:22:13,333 --> 00:22:15,791
[panting]

479
00:22:20,875 --> 00:22:23,458
[panting]

480
00:22:26,250 --> 00:22:27,333
[VICTOR]
Yuri.

481
00:22:27,416 --> 00:22:29,083
I've been thinking
about what I should do

482
00:22:29,166 --> 00:22:32,416
going forward as your coach.

483
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:34,125
[YURI]
Yeah, so have I.

484
00:22:39,791 --> 00:22:41,583
Victor, will you...

485
00:22:41,666 --> 00:22:43,916
...be my coach...

486
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,791
...until I retire?

487
00:22:48,416 --> 00:22:49,666
[VICTOR sighs]

488
00:22:51,791 --> 00:22:53,041
[VICTOR kisses]

489
00:22:53,125 --> 00:22:55,458
